    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ESM message header encoding/decoding bit field handling\n\n### Summary\nThe ESM message encoder in the NAS stack was not correctly handling bit fields in the message header due to unsafe casting operations. When encoding ESM messages, the protocol discriminator and EPS bearer identity fields were not being properly set in the first header byte, causing malformed messages to be sent over the air interface.\n\nThis fix replaces the unsafe bit field casting with explicit bit manipulation that properly handles endianness differences between little-endian and big-endian systems. Additionally, incorrect log message prefixes in the EMM decoder have been corrected.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/ESM/MSG/esm_msg.c`: Fixed bit field handling in `_esm_msg_encode_header` and `_esm_msg_decode_header` functions\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/emm_msg.c`: Corrected EMM-MSG log message prefixes\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure UE to establish a PDN connection\n2. Trigger ESM message encoding (e.g., by sending a PDN connectivity request)\n3. Observe that encoded messages have incorrect protocol discriminator values in the header\n4. Network rejects messages due to malformed headers\n\nThe issue manifests as ESM procedures failing to complete successfully, with messages being dropped by the network due to incorrect header formatting.\n"
}